Oyo State governor, Seyi Makinde and his Akwa Ibom State counterpart, Emmanuel Udom, are expected to grace the 38th Holy Ghost convention of the Sword of the Spirit Ministries International. According to the church, the governors are expected to be at the flag-off of the convention today (August 30), while the General Overseer of the Redeemed Church of God (RCCG), Pastor Enoch Adeboye, will anchor the dedication of the Wale Oke College of Missions and Evangelism (WOCOME) and the turning of sod of Tabernacle of David Cathedral both in Ibadan. Tribune Churchnews gathered that the convention will run from today (August 30) to September 6. The convention with the theme, ‘Landmark Blessings’,  which would be virtual in consonance with the COVID-19 protocols will feature the ministration of the visionary of the of the church, Bishop Francis Wale Oke, Pastor Adeboye, Nathaniel Bassey, Tope Alabi, Yomi Ajayi and Dunsi Oyekan, among others.  YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE CBN Pegs Exchange Rate At 386/$ Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) has pegged naira exchange rate at 386 units to the United States dollar as it plans to resume weekly forex sales to Bureau de Change operators from August 31. In a circular signed by O.S. Nnaji, director of trade and exchange department, the apex bank said its decision to resume FX sales to BDCs is to enhance accessibility to forex “particularly to travellers” since the resumption date for international… Council Of State Pardons Ex-Gov Ambrose Alli, Three Others The Council of State has ratified the presidential pardon extended to late former Bendel State Governor, Prof. Ambrose Alli and three others. The meeting presided over by President Muhammadu Buhari at the presidential villa, Abuja on Thursday also ratified the pardon granted to Col Moses Effiong, Major E.J Olarenwaju and… Blasphemy: I Will Not Hesitate To Sign Death Warrant If Yahya Sharif Fails To Appeal, Says Ganduje Kano State governor, Abdullahi Umar Ganduje